text: Greig Fraser, ACS, ASC, (born 3 October 1975) is an Australian cinematographer. His most well-known work are Zero Dark Thirty (2012), Lion (2016), Rogue One (2016), Vice (2018), and Dune (2021). In 2020, Fraser won a Primetime Emmy Award for his work on the television series The Mandalorian. He will also work on the 2022 DC Comics movie The Batman. ==References== Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:Cinematographers Category:People from Melbourne Category:Emmy Award winners
